comment: Galloway (NYK) affects Teague's (ATL) RSBQ at the start of the drive.
Scott (ATL) makes contact with Smith's (NYK) face during his layup attempt.
Hardaway Jr. (NYK) cleanly blocks Carroll's (ATL) layup attempt from behind, any contact that occurs after the block is considered incidental and does not affect the layup attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was touched simultaneously by Galloway (NYK) and Carroll (ATL) prior to going OOB was overturned, and New York was awarded possession.
Amundson (NYK) sets the screen on Korver (ATL) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
After Horford (ATL) cleanly knocks the ball away from Thomas (NYK), the two players make incidental foot to foot contact that causes Thomas to lose his balance.
Muscala (ATL) makes incidental contact with Smith (NYK) that does not affect his RSBQ prior to blocking the layup attempt.
Carroll (ATL) does not intentionally kick the ball on the play.
Smith (NYK) sets the screen on Teague (ATL) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Korver (ATL) makes "hi-five" contact with Thomas (NYK) after he releases the jump shot which is legal.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball hit the rim and the shot clock should be reset was upheld.
Teague (ATL) does not make contact with Galloway's (NYK) arm before ball is lost.
Carroll (ATL) commits a take foul on Hardaway Jr. (NYK).
Korver (ATL) commits a take foul on Smith (NYK).
Acy (NYK) maintains legal guarding position as Teague (ATL) initiates the incidental contact on the drive to the basket.
